title: Romania off to rough start at world gymnastics championships
text:
Matthias Schrader Romania off to rough start at world gymnastics championships 
Romania's Larisa Iordache performs during her beam routine as she takes part in the women's qualification competition at the World Artistic Gymnastics championships in Glasgow, Scotland, Friday, Oct. 23, 2015. (AP Photo/Matthias Schrader) Matthias Schrader Romania off to rough start at world gymnastics championships 
Romania's Larisa Iordache performs on the uneven bars as she takes part in the women's qualification competition at the World Artistic Gymnastics championships in Glasgow, Scotland, Friday, Oct. 23, 2015. (AP Photo/Matthias Schrader) Matthias Schrader Romania off to rough start at world gymnastics championships 
Uzbekistan's Oksana Chusovitina performs during her floor routine as she takes part in the women's qualification competition at the World Artistic Gymnastics championships in Glasgow, Scotland, Friday, Oct. 23, 2015. (AP Photo/Matthias Schrader) Posted: Friday, October 23, 2015 7:20 am | Updated: 7:45 am, Fri Oct 23, 2015. Romania off to rough start at world gymnastics championships Associated Press | 
GLASGOW, Scotland (AP) — The Romanian women's team is off to a nightmarish start at the world gymnastics championships. 
One of the sport's longtime powers stumbled through qualifying on Friday. Romania finished with a score 217.220, putting its chances of making the eight-team final next week in serious jeopardy.
